# Koyeb Deployment Configuration
# Restaurant Intelligence Platform
# 
# Deployment Instructions:
# 1. This is a monorepo with frontend (Next.js) and backend (Node.js/Express)
# 2. The main deployable service is the backend API server
# 3. Frontend can be deployed separately to Vercel or served statically
#
# Build Commands:
# - Backend: cd backend && npm install && npm run build
# - Frontend: cd frontend && npm install && npm run build
#
# Start Command:
# - Backend API: cd backend && npm start (runs on PORT from environment)
#
# Environment Variables Required:
# - DATABASE_URL (PostgreSQL connection string)
# - PORT (default: 3001)
# - NODE_ENV=production
# - All Toast POS API credentials
# - JWT_SECRET
# - CORS_ORIGIN (frontend URL)
#
# Health Check Endpoint:
# - GET /health (returns JSON with status)
#
# Main API Endpoints:
# - GET /api/test-connection (database test)
# - GET /api/restaurants (restaurant data)
# - GET /api/toast/* (Toast POS integration)

# Buildpack Detection
# This should be detected as a Node.js project due to package.json
# If not detected, use: heroku/nodejs buildpack

# For manual buildpack specification:
# echo 'heroku/nodejs' > .buildpacks